 it is deployed. Leading scholars from a range of disciplinary backgrounds examine how symbolic resources and cultural understandings help firms and regions develop. Through a thoughtful analysis of current- day cases, as well as historical developments, The Cultural Wealth of Nations offers an exciting new alternative to standard economic explanations about the wealth and poverty of nations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aCultural propertyxEconomic aspects. 0aCulturexEconomic aspects. 0aEconomic developmentxSocial aspects. 0aHeritage tourism. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Sociology / General.2bisacsh1 aBandelj, Nina, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aWherry, Frederick F., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978080478072840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780804780728423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780804780728.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles